	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have a Japanese Super Famicom with damaged OAM (object attribute memory, basically what tells it where sprites go and how to flip them.)
<br />
<br />As a result, you don't read back what you wrote to OAM, and sprites get all mixed up and flipped oddly.
<br />
<br />Not much can be done about it, the OAM is inside one of the PPU chips.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


